    {
        "content": "<p>the <code>have</code> is to make omega aware of that specific inequality, as the tactic otherwise treats terms that are exponentiation as atomic (i.e. all it knows about those terms is that the term is nonnegative, in this case we need to know the term is at least <code>1</code> )</p>",
